And the Savior said: “I have given you these things so that you may write them down and give them secretly to your fellow spirits. For this is the mystery of the immovable race.” And when the Savior had said these things, He ascended into the Light. And the disciples saw Him no more. And they were filled with great joy and returned to their companions, teaching them the mystery of the Light.
And the Savior said: “The perfect Man is the one who has received the Light and has become the Light. He who has the Light in himself will not be overcome by the darkness.”
And the Savior said: “The Light is the power of the Father. The darkness is the power of the rulers. The Light overcomes the darkness, and the darkness does not overcome the Light.”
