And when the Savior had said these things, He became invisible to them. But the disciples remained in great amazement, glorifying the Father and the Invisible Spirit who had sent the Anointed to reveal the hidden mysteries.
Then the Savior appeared to John as a youth, as an old man, and as a child, showing that He is the Formless One who takes all forms to teach humanity.
John, the brother of James, the sons of Zebedee, was troubled in spirit after the Savior’s ascension and went up to a mountain to pray. While praying, the heavens opened and a great light appeared, and the Savior revealed Himself in multiple forms.
This is the teaching which the Savior revealed to John, the son of Zebedee, concerning the perfect Father, the Invisible Spirit, the pleroma of light, and the fall of Sophia which brought forth this world of shadow.
The Savior said to John: “John, why do you doubt? Why are you afraid? I am the One who is with you always. I have come to reveal to you the things that are, the things that were, and the things that must come to pass.”
